The paper proposes a method for image inpainting using a generative multi-column network, which is a combination of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and generative models. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of a confidence-driven reconstruction loss and an implicit diversified MRF regularization, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the inpainting of natural objects and scenes, which could fall under the graphics (cs.GR) or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
